defs.docs: Miscellaneous tools for concurrent programming.

defs.name: atomic
defs.docs: Atomic types.

defs.name: AtomicCell
defs.docs: A thread-safe mutable memory location.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Creates a new atomic cell initialized with `val`.

defs.name: into_inner
defs.docs: Unwraps the atomic cell and returns its inner value.

defs.name: is_lock_free
defs.docs: Returns `true` if operations on values of this type are lock-free.

defs.name: store
defs.docs: Stores `val` into the atomic cell.

defs.name: swap
defs.docs: Stores `val` into the atomic cell and returns the previous value.

defs.name: as_ptr
defs.docs: Returns a raw pointer to the underlying data in this atomic cell.

defs.name: get_mut
defs.docs: Returns a mutable reference to the inner value.

attributes.value:
deprecated(note =
             "this method is unsound and will be removed in the next release")

defs.name: take
defs.docs: Takes the value of the atomic cell, leaving `Default::default()` in its place.

defs.name: load
defs.docs: Loads a value.

defs.name: compare_and_swap
defs.value: fn (&self, current: T, new: T) -> T
defs.docs: If the current value equals `current`, stores `new` into the atomic cell.

defs.name: compare_exchange
defs.value: fn (&self, current: T, new: T) -> Result<T, T>
defs.docs: If the current value equals `current`, stores `new` into the atomic cell.

defs.name: fetch_and
defs.docs: Applies logical "and" to the current value and returns the previous value.

defs.name: fetch_or
defs.docs: Applies logical "or" to the current value and returns the previous value.

defs.name: fetch_xor
defs.docs: Applies logical "xor" to the current value and returns the previous value.

defs.name: AtomicConsume
defs.docs: Trait which allows reading from primitive atomic types with "consume" ordering.

defs.name: Val
defs.docs: Type returned by `load_consume`.

defs.name: load_consume
defs.docs: Loads a value from the atomic using a "consume" memory ordering.

defs.name: CachePadded
defs.docs: Pads and aligns a value to the length of a cache line.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Pads and aligns a value to the length of a cache line.

defs.name: into_inner
defs.docs: Returns the inner value.

defs.name: Backoff
defs.docs: Performs exponential backoff in spin loops.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Creates a new `Backoff`.

defs.name: reset
defs.docs: Resets the `Backoff`.

defs.name: spin
defs.docs: Backs off in a lock-free loop.

defs.name: snooze
defs.docs: Backs off in a blocking loop.

defs.name: is_completed
defs.docs: Returns `true` if exponential backoff has completed and blocking the thread is advised.

defs.name: sync
defs.docs: Thread synchronization primitives.

defs.name: Parker
defs.docs: A thread parking primitive.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Creates a new `Parker`.

defs.name: park
defs.docs: Blocks the current thread until the token is made available.

defs.name: park_timeout
defs.docs: Blocks the current thread until the token is made available, but only for a limited time.

defs.name: unparker
defs.docs: Returns a reference to an associated [`Unparker`].

defs.name: Unparker
defs.docs: Unparks a thread parked by the associated [`Parker`].

defs.name: unpark
defs.docs: Atomically makes the token available if it is not already.

defs.name: ShardedLock
defs.docs: A sharded reader-writer lock.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Creates a new sharded reader-writer lock.

defs.name: into_inner
defs.docs: Consumes this lock, returning the underlying data.

defs.name: is_poisoned
defs.docs: Returns `true` if the lock is poisoned.

defs.name: get_mut
defs.docs: Returns a mutable reference to the underlying data.

defs.name: try_read
defs.docs: Attempts to acquire this lock with shared read access.

defs.name: read
defs.docs: Locks with shared read access, blocking the current thread until it can be acquired.

defs.name: try_write
defs.docs: Attempts to acquire this lock with exclusive write access.

defs.name: write
defs.docs: Locks with exclusive write access, blocking the current thread until it can be acquired.

defs.name: ShardedLockReadGuard
defs.docs: A guard used to release the shared read access of a [`ShardedLock`] when dropped.

defs.name: ShardedLockWriteGuard
defs.docs: A guard used to release the exclusive write access of a [`ShardedLock`] when dropped.

defs.name: WaitGroup
defs.docs: Enables threads to synchronize the beginning or end of some computation.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Creates a new wait group and returns the single reference to it.

defs.name: wait
defs.docs: Drops this reference and waits until all other references are dropped.

defs.name: thread
defs.docs: Threads that can borrow variables from the stack.

defs.name: scope
defs.docs: Creates a new scope for spawning threads.

defs.name: Scope
defs.docs: A scope for spawning threads.

defs.name: spawn
defs.value: fn <'scope, F, T> (&'scope self, f: F) -> ScopedJoinHandle<'scope, T>
defs.docs: Spawns a scoped thread.

defs.name: builder
defs.docs: Creates a builder that can configure a thread before spawning.

defs.name: ScopedThreadBuilder
defs.docs: Configures the properties of a new thread.

defs.name: name
defs.docs: Sets the name for the new thread.

defs.name: stack_size
defs.docs: Sets the size of the stack for the new thread.

defs.name: spawn
defs.value: fn <F, T> (self, f: F) -> io::Result<ScopedJoinHandle<'scope, T>>
defs.docs: Spawns a scoped thread with this configuration.

defs.name: ScopedJoinHandle
defs.docs: A handle that can be used to join its scoped thread.

defs.name: join
defs.docs: Waits for the thread to finish and returns its result.

defs.name: thread
defs.docs: Returns a handle to the underlying thread.
